The Hawks saved a 15-year-old girl from a forced marriage after her relatives allegedly sold her to a stranger. Three men aged 70, 51 and 26 were arrested and appeared in the Mthatha Magistrate s Court yesterday.According to Hawks spokeswoman Captain Anelisa Feni, the two older suspects were relatives of the teenager, while the 26-year-old had allegedly bought her to be his wife.For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions